news.title: Pune: Properties with solar water heating systems double in five years
news.para: While the number of properties with solar water heating systems stood at 29,000 in the year 2017-18, it surged to 58,000 in 2021-22, the report stated.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body ranks second in digitisation of property records in Karnataka
news.para: The HDMC, which regulates the infrastructural assets and civic facilities in the twin cities of Hubballi and Dharwad including properties, transactions and their administration, had launched an online management system that keeps a record of property ownership, transactions and status.

news.title: DTP demolishes encroachments, illegal colony in Panchkula
news.para: District planning officer (DTP) Gunjan Verma said that the drive was conducted under the Controlled Urban Area Act and Urban Area Act of the Town and Country Planning department.

news.title: Municipal chiefs, additional DCs can now issue CLUs, approve layouts in Punjab
news.para: Building plans would be cleared by municipal commissioners in case of municipal corporations and EOs in case of municipal councils, nagar panchayats and improvement trusts.

news.title: Property tax to be based on zones in Coimbatore
news.para: Zone-based tax will be applicable for buildings approved after July 1, 2022. Owners of existing buildings will continue to pay revised property taxes.

news.title: Online property tax payment hits Deolali Cantonment Board's revenue
news.para: The residents of the cantonment board area can pay property tax, other cess and fees only through the ‘echhawani’ portal.

news.title: HDFC hikes lending rate by 25 bps; home loan to be costlier
news.para: ​The rate hike comes ahead of the RBI's Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) meeting later next week. It is widely expected that MPC would hike interest rates to tame high inflation.

news.title: SC grants status quo in bungalow vs building row of Mumbai's Ghatkopar society
news.para: The bungalow owners had filed a suit in 2016 against BMC, executive engineer building proposals, a cooperative Housing Society in Ghatkopar and a developer.

news.title: Jaipur development body-JMRC row over, plot owners to get lease deeds soon
news.para: JDA had earlier sought directions from the UDH department for issuing lease deeds and carrying out development work in Metro Enclave.

news.title: YEIDA master plan 2041 may be ready in a week
news.para: Arun Veer Singh, the YEIDA CEO, said, “The master plan will be presented during the YEIDA board meeting for discussion.

news.title: Faridabad civic body closes gate of society with 3,000 flats, says it is built on govt's land
news.para: This is because the Municipal Corporation of Faridabad (MCF) has sealed one of the two gates, claiming encroachment of corporation land around it by the developer.

news.title: Gurugram: 22 builders get notices for using diesel generators sets
news.para: The temporary connection cannot be upgraded in absence of electrical infrastructure. The developers are supposed to submit a bank guarantee and provide 500 square yards of land for the construction of the switching station.

news.title: CBI seizes AgustaWestland helicopter from Pune premises of builder Avinash Bhosale
news.para: RKW Developers Pvt Ltd, which is owned by the Wadhawan family of DHFL Group, had allegedly joined the Association in 2017 by paying crores of rupees for the membership and maintenance of the chopper, they said.

news.title: Unitech founder Ramesh Chandra granted medical bail by Delhi HC
news.para: The court noted that from the medical record, it was clear that Chandra's condition was "quite serious" and his ailments "have assumed larger proportions" on account of age.

news.title: Evergrande offers sweetener for debt revamp as China property crisis worsens
news.para: Evergrande's restructuring proposal, which was thin in details, comes as China's property sector, a key pillar for the world's second-largest economy, lurches from one crisis to another. The sector has seen a string of debt defaults by cash-squeezed developers.
